而那个东西
And that thing,

191
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:25,188
你在夜总会看到我杀死的那个…
that you saw me kill at the club, that...

192
00:18:26,189 --> 00:18:28,066
也是一只邪灵
That was also a demon.

193
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:31,152
邪灵会附身任何活物
Demons can take possession of any living creature.

194
00:18:31,236 --> 00:18:33,154
你谁都不能信
You can't trust anyone.

195
00:18:33,238 --> 00:18:35,573
即使那人你很熟悉
Even people you think you know.

196
00:18:35,657 --> 00:18:37,742
那我干嘛要信你？
So, why should I trust you?

197
00:18:42,747 --> 00:18:44,666
因为我刚才救过你
I did just save your life.

198
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:50,338
多萝西，快开开门
Dorothea, open up, please.

199
00:18:53,383 --> 00:18:54,425
你能…
Can you...

200
00:18:58,346 --> 00:19:00,890
你知道我妈发生了什么吗？
Do you know what happened to my mom?

201
00:19:04,686 --> 00:19:05,895
你知道吗？
Do you?

202
00:19:07,522 --> 00:19:08,946
等等，你可以看到他？
Wait, you can see this guy?

203
00:19:08,946 --> 00:19:10,608
当然可以 她是女巫
Of course she can. She's a witch.

204
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:17,699
从姜饼套房降级到了单卧室？
Downgraded from a gingerbread house to a one-bedroom?

205
00:19:18,241 --> 00:19:19,659
你知道我妈在哪里吗？
Do you know where my mom is?

206
00:19:19,742 --> 00:19:21,327
对不起，我不清楚
Sorry. I have no idea.

207
00:19:21,411 --> 00:19:24,080
嗯，她曾提到一个名字… 瓦伦丁
Well, she mentioned a name... Valentine.

208
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:27,041
- 你最好离开  - 不，请不要这样
- You better leave. - No, please.

209
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:29,961
你不告诉我，我就不走
Not until you tell me something, anything.

210
00:19:59,532 --> 00:20:01,492
看看骨牌占卜到什么
Let's see what the cards have to say.

211
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:04,037
对不起，我不信这些…
I'm sorry, but you know that I don't believe in any of...

212
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:05,246
坐下
Sit.

213
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:09,500
把手在牌上过一遍
Run your hands over the cards.

214
00:20:14,589 --> 00:20:16,090
我妈妈画过这些
My mom painted these.

215
00:20:16,174 --> 00:20:17,842
是的，你妈妈送的
Yes. They were a gift.

216
00:20:19,219 --> 00:20:21,888
看看你拿到哪一张牌
Let's see which card gets picked.

217
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:50,166
大金杯
The Ace of Cups.

218
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,919
- 那是圣杯  - 那？
- That's the Mortal Cup. - So?

219
00:20:53,002 --> 00:20:54,087
别理他
Ignore him.

220
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:55,081
这是圣杯神器
It's a Mortal Instrument,

221
00:20:55,081 --> 00:20:56,589
我们族人三大圣物之一
one of the three holy objects of my people.

222
00:20:56,673 --> 00:20:57,757
它怎么在这儿？
What's it doing here?

223
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:00,093
我不明白这跟我妈有什么关联
I don't understand what any of this has to do with my mom.

224
00:21:00,176 --> 00:21:03,096
你母亲是暗影猎人，跟他一样
Your mother was a Shadowhunter, like him.

225
00:21:03,513 --> 00:21:05,473
不，我妈是个画家
No, my mom is a painter.

226
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:07,725
她从没跟你说过，对吧？
She never told you any of this, did she?

227
00:21:07,809 --> 00:21:09,277
我只知道的是她消失了
All I know is that she's gone,

228
00:21:09,277 --> 00:21:11,646
然后我不知道去哪里找她
and I have no idea where to start looking for her.

229
00:21:15,066 --> 00:21:16,526
让我给你读心
Let me read you.

230
00:21:39,549 --> 00:21:42,135
有东西封印了你的回忆
There's something blocking your mind.

231
00:21:42,552 --> 00:21:45,805
我猜是你妈妈雇请了高人来保护你
My guess is your mother hired someone very skilled to protect you.

232
00:21:45,888 --> 00:21:47,932
- 保护什么？  - 你的回忆
- From what? - Your own memories.

233
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,226
为什么？
Why?

234
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:53,271
我不懂她要我忘记什么
I don't remember anything she'd want me to forget.

235
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:14,876
等等
Wait.

236
00:22:15,877 --> 00:22:17,420
很高兴见到你
Nice to meet you.

237
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,851
搞什么？
What the hell?

238
00:22:32,518 --> 00:22:33,978
你吓到我了
You scared me.

239
00:22:34,062 --> 00:22:36,189
这究竟发生过什么？
What the hell happened here?

240
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,025
- 我妈妈不见了  - 什么？
- My mom's missing. - What?

241
00:22:39,108 --> 00:22:41,944
有人抓了她，还毁了这里
Someone took her and destroyed the place.

242
00:22:46,908 --> 00:22:49,577
他正帮我找她
This guy is helping me find her,

243
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:52,121
你看不到他，而且他…
but you can't see him, and he...

244
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:54,457
克拉蕾
Clary.

245
00:22:55,291 --> 00:22:56,501
好吧
Great.

246
00:22:56,584 --> 00:22:58,461
好吧，现在我也看不到他了
Okay, now I can't see him, either.

247
00:23:00,129 --> 00:23:02,215
杰斯·维兰德，邪灵猎手
Jace Wayland, demon hunter.

248
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:07,345
西蒙·卢易斯，解锁师
Simon Lewis, Keymaster.

249
00:23:07,428 --> 00:23:08,475
你是门卫吗？
Are you the Gatekeeper?

250
00:23:08,475 --> 00:23:10,264
我不懂你在说什么
I have no idea what you're talking about.

251
00:23:10,348 --> 00:23:13,059
等等 什么，你现在可以看到他了？
Wait. What, so you can see him now?

252
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:15,019
- 什么？我当然能看到他  - 可我以为…
- What? Of course I can see him. - But I thought...

253
00:23:15,103 --> 00:23:16,771
- 不…  - 你说什么呢？
- No... - What are you talking about?

254
00:23:16,854 --> 00:23:18,398
我被搞糊涂了
This is so confusing.

255
00:23:19,148 --> 00:23:20,316
这是谁？
Who's this?

256
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:22,860
我爸爸，我两岁时他就死了
That's my dad. He died when I was two.

257
00:23:29,450 --> 00:23:31,035
克拉蕾，等等
Clary, a moment.

258
00:23:31,119 --> 00:23:33,278
等等，你妈消失了
So, wait, your mom is gone,

259
00:23:33,876 --> 00:23:38,000
你却跟这染金发的追星小伙在一起？
and you're hanging around with some dyed-blond wannabe Goth weirdo?

260
00:23:38,709 --> 00:23:40,294
你在哪儿遇到他的？
Where'd you come across this guy?

261
00:23:40,378 --> 00:23:43,840
- 不，我没有 是他找我的  - 什么？他找你
- No, I didn't. He found me. - What? He found you?

262
00:23:43,923 --> 00:23:46,217
- 不，我知道这听起来…  - 看看这个
- No, I know it sounds... - You should check this.

263
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:48,469
郑重声明，我头发金色是天生的
And for the record, my hair is naturally blond.

264
00:23:51,097 --> 00:23:54,350
克拉蕾，克拉蕾，克拉蕾… 西蒙？
Clary, Clary, Clary... Simon?

265
00:23:55,059 --> 00:23:56,144
她打过电话？
She called you?

266
00:23:57,645 --> 00:23:58,980
你为什么不接？
Why didn't you pick up?

267
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,691
要是知道这么严重，我早接了
If I'd known it was serious, I would have picked up.

268
00:24:01,774 --> 00:24:03,860
你都没接怎么会知道？
Well, how would you know if you didn't pick it up?

269
00:24:06,863 --> 00:24:08,281
那是什么？
What's that?

270
00:24:11,242 --> 00:24:12,618
没好事
Nothing good.

271
00:24:13,161 --> 00:24:15,121
你懂她哪儿弄来这个的吗？
Do you have any idea where she got this?

272
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:16,998
我得找卢克
I've got to find Luke.

273
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:30,136
太奇怪了，他车在这儿
It's so weird. His truck's here.

274
00:24:30,428 --> 00:24:31,762
来吧 这边
Come on. This way.

275
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:35,316
不，你在这等
No, you wait here.

276
00:24:35,316 --> 00:24:36,851
干嘛要听你的？
Who made you the boss?

277
00:24:37,602 --> 00:24:40,396
没关系，这样有人来能通知我们
It's okay. Just let us know if anyone comes.

278
00:24:41,230 --> 00:24:43,305
我认识卢克好多年
I've known Luke all these years,

279
00:24:43,305 --> 00:24:45,193
但我都没下来过
but I've never been down here.

280
00:24:54,827 --> 00:24:55,995
什么？
What?

281
00:24:56,537 --> 00:24:58,080
快点，伙计！
Come on, mate!

282
00:25:09,842 --> 00:25:11,511
伙计，听好…
Now, listen...

283
00:25:11,886 --> 00:25:14,847
你要做的就是说真话
All you got to do, mate, is tell me the truth.

284
00:25:14,931 --> 00:25:17,350
我说了，不知道圣杯在哪儿
I'm telling you, I don't know where the Cup is.

285
00:25:17,433 --> 00:25:19,560
我知道你和乔丝关系好
I know you and Jocie are close.

286
00:25:19,644 --> 00:25:21,437
我可不是傻子？
I'm not stupid, am I?

287
00:25:21,896 --> 00:25:23,564
别这样回答
Don't answer that.

288
00:25:23,898 --> 00:25:25,141
听我说，伙计
Listen to me, mate.

289
00:25:25,141 --> 00:25:27,443
只要告诉我圣杯在哪儿
Just tell me where the Mortal Cup is.

290
00:25:28,152 --> 00:25:30,029
乔丝就会没事
And then Jocie will be fine.

291
00:25:30,112 --> 00:25:32,664
卢克，说啊，告诉我
Lukey, tell me. Tell me the truth.

292
00:25:32,664 --> 00:25:33,699
我不知道
I don't know.

293
00:25:33,783 --> 00:25:35,868
你可别惹我生气
You don't want to make me angry.

294
00:25:35,952 --> 00:25:38,162
- 我说了…  - 是吗？
- I'm telling you... - Do you?

295
00:25:39,455 --> 00:25:41,698
我再问一遍，伙计
I'm going to ask you again, mate,

296
00:25:41,698 --> 00:25:43,084
圣杯在哪儿？
where's the Cup, huh?

297
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:44,669
我不知道
I don't know.

298
00:25:44,835 --> 00:25:48,339
我们都需要它，卢克，不是吗？
We all want the same thing, Lukey boy, don't we?

299
00:25:48,422 --> 00:25:52,009
不同之处，我觉得你知道它在哪儿
Difference is, I think you know where it is.

300
00:25:52,218 --> 00:25:53,386
不是吗？
Don't you?

301
00:25:53,469 --> 00:25:55,471
快点 快点 说啊！
Come on. Come on. Talk!

302
00:25:55,555 --> 00:25:58,307
- 我们得走了  - 不，求你了，你要帮他
- We need to go. - No, please, you have to help him.

303
00:25:58,391 --> 00:25:59,684
你不懂
You don't understand.

304
00:26:00,476 --> 00:26:02,061
他们是瓦伦丁的人
They work for Valentine.

305
00:26:02,812 --> 00:26:04,804
他是个死人 我帮不了他
He's a dead man. I can't help him.

306
00:26:04,804 --> 00:26:05,773
他是我家人
He's like family.

307
00:26:05,856 --> 00:26:07,567
奇了怪
You know what's really amazing

308
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:10,570
你看上去还挺像人类
is how much you actually look like a human.

309
00:26:11,153 --> 00:26:12,697
很棒啊？
Isn't it great?

310
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,328
求你了
Please.

311
00:26:19,412 --> 00:26:21,205
你要发狂了？你要变身了？
Are you gonna get mad? You're going to change?

312
00:26:21,289 --> 00:26:22,665
我要看你变身
I want to see you change.

313
00:26:23,833 --> 00:26:26,168
给我露露你怎么变身的？
Show me how you can change. Huh?

314
00:26:26,252 --> 00:26:28,504
看看 看看
Look at that. Look at that.

315
00:26:30,256 --> 00:26:31,674
狼人来了
Dog boy's coming on.

316
00:26:31,757 --> 00:26:32,925
你想搞我腿？
You want to hump my leg?

317
00:26:33,384 --> 00:26:35,678
你搞我腿？喜欢这样？
You hump legs? You like that?

318
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:38,097
要嗅我屁股吗？
You want to smell my derriere?

319
00:26:41,601 --> 00:26:43,603
我要看你　变身
I want to see you change!

320
00:26:44,437 --> 00:26:46,939
告诉我乔丝琳把圣杯藏哪儿
You just got to tell me where Jocelyn hid the Cup.

321
00:26:47,023 --> 00:26:48,941
然后你可以平安带回她
Then you can have her back.

322
00:26:49,025 --> 00:26:50,693
她会平安无事的
She'll be safe and sound.

323
00:26:53,362 --> 00:26:55,489
我没要她回来
I don't want her back.

324
00:26:55,573 --> 00:26:57,158
我一点不在乎
I couldn't care less.

325
00:26:57,241 --> 00:26:59,600
我这么多年
I have spent years

326
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:02,580
一直在讨好她和她的倔女儿，就是为圣杯
cozying up to that woman and her brat for the Mortal Cup.

327
00:27:03,289 --> 00:27:05,333
潘伯恩，听我说
Pangborn, listen to me.

328
00:27:05,416 --> 00:27:08,002
我也想把圣杯给瓦伦丁
I want to be the one to give her to Valentine.

329
00:27:08,127 --> 00:27:09,545
呀，对
Yeah, right.

330
00:27:12,757 --> 00:27:15,217
你在犯大错
You are making a big mistake.

331
00:27:15,301 --> 00:27:17,428
我不信，你信他吗？
I don't believe you. Do you believe him?

332
00:27:25,102 --> 00:27:26,646
- 克拉蕾，快跑！  - 克拉蕾，听我说！
- Clary, run!          - Clary, listen!

333
00:27:38,366 --> 00:27:40,534
劳驾 警官？
Excuse me. Officer?

334
00:27:41,243 --> 00:27:43,204
我要报案，有人闯入
I'd like to report a break-in.

335
00:27:43,746 --> 00:27:45,206
一人失踪
And a missing person.

336
00:28:25,454 --> 00:28:27,623
有人闯入我朋友的家…
My friend's house got broken into, and...

337
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:31,419
- 她妈妈失踪了  - 哦，不
- Her mom's missing. - Oh, no.

338
00:28:31,919 --> 00:28:33,295
快跑！
Run!

339
00:28:43,931 --> 00:28:46,267
- 你杀了两个警察！  - 他们不是警察
- You killed two cops! - They weren't cops.

340
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:47,560
快走！
Let's go!

341
00:28:59,071 --> 00:29:00,322
克拉蕾
Clary.

342
00:29:01,323 --> 00:29:03,325
你不能留在这儿 他们会抓到你的
You can't stay here. They'll find you.

343
00:29:04,702 --> 00:29:07,288
卢克怎么会说他不在乎？
How could Luke say that he didn't care?

344
00:29:07,371 --> 00:29:10,040
我从记事起就认识他了
I've known him for as long as I can remember.

345
00:29:10,124 --> 00:29:11,805
他曾每晚都为我读故事
He used to read to me every night.

346
00:29:11,805 --> 00:29:13,919
他天天来校接我好几年了
He's been picking me up at school for years.

347
00:29:14,003 --> 00:29:16,672
也许这记忆不真实
Look, maybe those memories aren't real.

348
00:29:17,214 --> 00:29:19,341
你不记得我说的了吗？
Do you remember what I told you?

349
00:29:19,425 --> 00:29:21,343
谁都不能相信
You can't trust anyone.

350
00:29:22,678 --> 00:29:24,221
不，我要找回妈妈，我要回家
No, I need to find my mom. I have to go home.

351
00:29:24,305 --> 00:29:26,432
- 我肯定漏了什么！  - 听我说，好吗？
- There must be something that I missed! - Listen to me, okay?

352
00:29:26,515 --> 00:29:28,517
我们会弄清的，但不是此时此地
We'll figure this out, but not here and not now.

353
00:29:28,601 --> 00:29:31,228
你得到一个安全的地方
We need to get you to a safe place.

354
00:29:31,395 --> 00:29:32,878
我是暗影猎人，克拉蕾
I'm a Shadowhunter, Clary,

355
00:29:32,878 --> 00:29:34,857
我会誓死保护你
and I will protect you with my life.

356
00:29:36,025 --> 00:29:38,319
你们在这儿，我以为你们紧跟着
There you guys are. I thought you were right behind me.

357
00:29:38,402 --> 00:29:39,904
我丢了你们
I thought I'd lost you.

358
00:29:39,987 --> 00:29:42,448
好吧，我跟着你
Okay. I'll follow you.

359
00:29:42,531 --> 00:29:44,742
你确定吗？他刚杀了两个警察
Are you sure about that? 'Cause he just killed two cops.

360
00:29:44,825 --> 00:29:46,035
呀，他们不是警察
Yeah, they weren't cops.

361
00:29:47,077 --> 00:29:49,121
我觉得他们就是
They looked like real cops to me.

362
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:51,540
- 他们不是真警察  - 好吧
- They weren't real cops. - Okay.

363
00:29:53,167 --> 00:29:55,461
那他们那儿弄来的警车？
So, where did they get the car?

364
00:29:58,631 --> 00:30:00,591
他们不是真警察
They weren't real cops.

365
00:30:10,643 --> 00:30:12,520
在这我们会很安全
We'll be safe in here.

366
00:30:12,728 --> 00:30:14,396
这鬼地方是哪里？
What is this dump?

367
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:16,273
这不是鬼地方
This isn't a dump.

368
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:19,443
只不过你看不见
You just can't see it.

369
00:30:53,018 --> 00:30:55,813
到底怎么了？他们做了什么？
What the hell is going on? What are they doing in here?

370
00:30:56,272 --> 00:30:57,773
- 这是被邪灵咬伤  - 克拉蕾
- It's a demon bite. - Clary.

371
00:30:58,440 --> 00:30:59,775
杰斯，做点什么！
Jace, do something!

372
00:30:59,859 --> 00:31:02,243
接下来是不是你该撕掉你的衬衣
Is this the part when you start tearing off pieces of your shirt

373
00:31:02,243 --> 00:31:03,779
包扎我的伤口呢？
to bind my wounds?

374
00:31:04,530 --> 00:31:06,021
如果你要我把这身衣服脱下来
If you wanted me to take my clothes off,

375
00:31:06,021 --> 00:31:07,449
只要你发话就行
you should've just asked.

376
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:18,419
只是有点发烧
It's just a fever.

377
00:31:26,719 --> 00:31:28,637
她醒了
She's waking up.

378
00:31:50,117 --> 00:31:52,114
我昏倒后你们给纹的？
I passed out, and you guys tattooed me?

379
00:31:52,114 --> 00:31:53,913
我以为这只在赌城才会发生
Thought that only happened in Vegas.

380
00:31:53,996 --> 00:31:55,664
- 这不是纹身  - 是图符
- It's not a tattoo. - It's a rune.

381
00:31:55,748 --> 00:31:57,233
它让你拥有一切：
They have them for everything,

382
00:31:57,233 --> 00:31:59,293
隐身术，强健之躯和自愈术
they make you invisible, strong, they heal.

383
00:31:59,376 --> 00:32:00,708
它让你可见
They also make you visible.

384
00:32:00,708 --> 00:32:02,421
所以我突然可以看到他
That's why I could suddenly see him.

385
00:32:02,504 --> 00:32:04,590
- 即使你不吃饭…  - 不
- Even if you're hungry... - No.

386
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:09,887
事实上，这图符是让你可以看到我们
The fact that the rune had an effect on you explains why you can see us.

387
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:11,096
我没弄懂
I don't get it.

388
00:32:11,180 --> 00:32:12,918
凡人是挺不过来的
Mundanes can't survive the process.

389
00:32:12,918 --> 00:32:14,850
他们无法承受这图符的力量，所以…
The runes are too strong for them, so...

390
00:32:14,934 --> 00:32:16,977
现在，我们很确定你有暗影猎人的血脉
Now we definitely know you have Shadowhunter blood.

391
00:32:17,061 --> 00:32:18,771
等等，那之前就不确定了？
Wait, it wasn't definite before?

392
00:32:18,854 --> 00:32:21,398
她没死，才让我们更确定，是这样的
Well, it became definite when she didn't die. Yes.

393
00:32:22,024 --> 00:32:24,068
看看合不合身
Here, see if these fit.

394
00:32:24,151 --> 00:32:26,070
我们这不是天天有贵客的
It's not every day we get guests in here.

395
00:32:26,153 --> 00:32:27,947
尤其少见女客人
Especially not girls.

396
00:32:30,616 --> 00:32:31,700
是啊
Yeah.

397
00:32:39,375 --> 00:32:41,251
我们要叫警察来吗？
Shouldn't we call the cops?

398
00:32:41,335 --> 00:32:43,212
我指的是真警察
I mean, the real ones.

399
00:32:43,545 --> 00:32:44,408
好主意
That's a great idea.

400
00:32:44,408 --> 00:32:46,382
我只是不懂我们为何没想到过
I just don't know why we haven't thought of that

401
00:32:46,465 --> 00:32:48,592
在过去的这几千年中
for the past thousand years.

402
00:32:49,927 --> 00:32:51,845
霍奇在等她
Hodge is ready for her.

403
00:32:52,763 --> 00:32:55,265
他想在藏书馆单独见她
He wants to see her alone in the library.

404
00:32:56,475 --> 00:32:57,768
霍奇是谁？
Who's Hodge?

405
00:32:58,227 --> 00:32:59,895
他是这里的头
He's in charge of the Institute.

406
00:33:00,604 --> 00:33:01,814
好吧，我们走
Okay, let's go.

407
00:33:02,439 --> 00:33:05,275
无数的暗影猎人曾来此寻求庇护
Hundreds of Shadowhunters used to seek asylum here.

408
00:33:05,359 --> 00:33:07,111
但你也看到了
But, as you can see,

409
00:33:07,403 --> 00:33:09,655
现在只剩我们这几个了
right now, we're the only ones.

410
00:33:09,738 --> 00:33:12,658
没有圣杯，我们只能等死
Without the Mortal Cup, we're a dying breed.

411
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:15,369
要么你是暗影猎人的后代
Either you're born of a Shadowhunter,

412
00:33:15,452 --> 00:33:17,913
要么你有喝过圣杯之水
or you have to drink from the Mortal Cup.

413
00:33:25,045 --> 00:33:26,422
你来自
You coming?

414
00:33:29,758 --> 00:33:32,177
遥远的布鲁克林，对吧？
Pretty far from Brooklyn, isn't it?

415
00:33:33,220 --> 00:33:34,972
离杰斯远点
Stay away from Jace.

416
00:33:40,269 --> 00:33:42,521
你可能觉得霍奇有点古怪
You may find Hodge a little eccentric,

417
00:33:42,604 --> 00:33:45,899
但他曾是最出色的暗影猎人之一
but he's one of the greatest Shadowhunters that's ever lived.

418
00:33:45,983 --> 00:33:47,693
这给我
Here, give me that.

419
00:34:26,315 --> 00:34:28,233
你不觉得这有点冒险
Don't you think it's a bit risky

420
00:34:28,317 --> 00:34:29,863
让一个完全陌生的人
inviting a complete stranger

421
00:34:29,863 --> 00:34:31,570
闯进神院中心？
into the heart of the Institute?

422
00:34:31,653 --> 00:34:34,239
不，我们可以相信她
No. I think we can trust her.

423
00:34:34,323 --> 00:34:35,866
那她的凡人朋友呢？
And what about her mundane friend?

424
00:34:35,949 --> 00:34:37,409
嗯，这是一时疏忽
Well, that was impulsive.

425
00:34:37,826 --> 00:34:39,745
你一时疏忽，会弄砸事
When you're impulsive, things go badly.

426
00:34:45,250 --> 00:34:46,175
当心
Just be careful,

427
00:34:46,175 --> 00:34:49,171
自愈心碎的图符是最疼的
the rune to fix a broken heart is the most painful one.

428
00:34:49,755 --> 00:34:52,549
我保证适时让他们离开
They'll be out of here in a day, I promise.

429
00:34:59,431 --> 00:35:00,682
杰斯
Jace.

430
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:08,440
她曾是最出色的猎人之一
She was one of the best,

431
00:35:08,732 --> 00:35:10,025
你的母亲
your mum.

432
00:35:10,692 --> 00:35:12,277
但我不明白为什么她…
But I don't understand why...

433
00:35:12,361 --> 00:35:15,572
昨天你还只是个普通的女孩
Yesterday you were just a normal girl.

434
00:35:15,656 --> 00:35:17,241
今天仿佛感觉到
Today you feel as though

435
00:35:17,324 --> 00:35:20,202
你的世界彻底翻天覆地改变了
your whole world has been turned upside down.

436
00:35:24,706 --> 00:35:27,209
你必须知道一件事
There's only one thing you need to know.

437
00:35:28,043 --> 00:35:31,046
那是你小时候听到的故事
The stories you were told as a little girl

438
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:33,048
怪兽和梦魇
about monsters, nightmares,

439
00:35:33,382 --> 00:35:36,426
篝火旁低诉的传说…
legends whispered around campfires...

440
00:35:37,886 --> 00:35:39,054
他们都是真的
They're all true.

441
00:35:41,473 --> 00:35:43,225
- 邪灵？  - 对
- Demon?    - Yes.

442
00:35:47,563 --> 00:35:48,814
邪灵？
Demon?

443
00:35:48,897 --> 00:35:50,482
不，狼人不是邪灵
No. Werewolves aren't demons.

444
00:35:50,566 --> 00:35:52,985
我们和地下生物有过停战协议
We have a truce with Downworlders.

445
00:35:53,068 --> 00:35:54,319
地下生物？
Downworlders?

446
00:35:54,403 --> 00:35:57,197
是什么？14号街以下的人？
What is that, like people below 14th Street?

447
00:35:57,281 --> 00:35:59,616
嗯，“地下生物”包括很多
Well, "Downworlders" pretty much sums everything up,

448
00:35:59,700 --> 00:36:02,327
吸血鬼，狼人和术士
vampires, werewolves, Warlocks.

449
00:36:02,411 --> 00:36:04,163
术士，很酷啊
Warlocks. Cool.

450
00:36:05,038 --> 00:36:06,832
你怎么杀死一只僵尸的？
So, how do you kill a zombie?

451
00:36:06,915 --> 00:36:08,000
我们没杀
We don't.

452
00:36:08,083 --> 00:36:09,835
当然他们已经死了
Of course, they're already dead.

453
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:11,712
不，他们不存在
No. They don't exist.

454
00:36:13,922 --> 00:36:16,508
那么这就是大家所说的圣杯吧
So, that's the famous Cup everyone's talking about.

455
00:36:16,592 --> 00:36:18,719
只是个模型，不过也对
A replica. But yes.

456
00:36:20,846 --> 00:36:24,183
那你知道杰斯敏感易怒咯
You know, Jace has got a real chip on his shoulder.

457
00:36:24,266 --> 00:36:24,933
你也一样的
You would, too,

458
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:27,186
如果你小时候亲眼看到你父亲被杀
if you saw your father murdered when you were a child.

459
00:36:27,269 --> 00:36:29,021
要不是他，我们全死了
If it weren't for him, we'd be dead.

460
00:36:29,104 --> 00:36:32,357
我都说不清他救了我们多少次了
He saved our lives more times than I care to admit.

461
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:34,526
好吧
Right.

462
00:36:40,324 --> 00:36:41,950
据传说
The legend goes,

463
00:36:42,576 --> 00:36:45,621
十字军曾召唤过一位天使
the Crusaders summoned an angel,

464
00:36:46,496 --> 00:36:48,123
天使拉齐尔
the Angel Raziel.

465
00:36:48,832 --> 00:36:51,251
拉齐尔将自己的鲜血倒入圣杯
Raziel poured his blood into a cup,

466
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:53,151
那些喝过其血的人
and those who drank from it

467
00:36:53,151 --> 00:36:54,963
变成半天使，半凡人
became half angel, half human.

468
00:36:55,297 --> 00:36:56,798
暗影猎人
Shadowhunters.

469
00:36:57,466 --> 00:37:00,427
这会遗传给他们的子子孙孙
As did their children and their children's children.

470
00:37:00,802 --> 00:37:02,638
有强大力量的族群
Beings of immense power,

471
00:37:02,763 --> 00:37:05,098
足以恢复和平
strong enough to restore balance

472
00:37:05,182 --> 00:37:08,560
保护世界，抵御邪灵
and protect the world in a war against evil.

473
00:37:08,644 --> 00:37:10,896
这是无赢家的斗争
A war that can never be won,

474
00:37:12,105 --> 00:37:14,316
但永无休止
but must always be fought.

475
00:37:16,235 --> 00:37:18,403
因为邪灵永生不息
Demons don't die easily.

476
00:37:19,821 --> 00:37:23,659
但我们却终有一死
Whereas we, we remained all too mortal.

477
00:37:24,117 --> 00:37:25,870
你们干嘛不用圣杯
Why didn't they just use the Cup

478
00:37:25,870 --> 00:37:27,412
繁衍出更多的暗影猎人？
to create more Shadowhunters?

479
00:37:27,496 --> 00:37:29,122
瓦伦丁也这么说过
Valentine's exact words.

480
00:37:29,539 --> 00:37:31,750
克拉夫－圣杯守护者
The Clave, the keepers of the Cup,

481
00:37:31,833 --> 00:37:33,752
他们害怕其力量
they were afraid of using its power.

482
00:37:33,835 --> 00:37:36,797
他们知道没人能承受住圣杯的力量而存活
They knew that hardly anyone who drank from it survived.

483
00:37:37,673 --> 00:37:41,343
瓦伦丁·摩根斯坦召集了一群朋友
Valentine Morgenstern drew a circle of friends together,

484
00:37:41,677 --> 00:37:44,596
一群年轻妄想的暗影猎人
young, idealistic Shadowhunters,

485
00:37:47,224 --> 00:37:50,686
帮他从克拉夫手里偷到了圣杯
to help him steal the Mortal Cup from the Clave.

486
00:37:53,105 --> 00:37:55,816
但瓦伦丁并不想保护人类
But he didn't want to protect humanity.

487
00:37:56,858 --> 00:38:00,445
他相信暗影猎人可以进化
He believed there had to be an evolution of Shadowhunters,

488
00:38:00,529 --> 00:38:02,197
变得更具力量
something more powerful.

489
00:38:02,281 --> 00:38:05,033
他开始试着使用圣杯
He began experimenting, using the Mortal Cup.

490
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:08,453
并学会了召唤邪灵
He learned how to summon demons.

491
00:38:10,622 --> 00:38:12,896
他甚至给自己注射过邪灵的鲜血
He even injected himself with demon blood

492
00:38:12,896 --> 00:38:14,251
以此来控制他们
so he could control them.

493
00:38:15,544 --> 00:38:17,254
他想统治一切
He wanted to rule.

494
00:38:19,214 --> 00:38:21,258
为了阻止他，你妈妈
Your mother, to prevent that,

495
00:38:21,341 --> 00:38:23,635
偷走了圣杯
stole the Cup from him,

496
00:38:23,719 --> 00:38:25,387
而后消失不见
and vanished into thin air.

497
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:28,432
但要是只有她知道圣杯在哪里，那么…
But if she's the only one that knows where the Cup is, then...

498
00:38:28,557 --> 00:38:30,225
也许不只她
Maybe she isn't.

499
00:38:30,309 --> 00:38:32,477
她可能告诉某人了
Maybe she told someone else.

500
00:38:33,979 --> 00:38:36,231
一个没有人猜到她知道的人
Someone who doesn't know she knows.

501
00:38:40,944 --> 00:38:42,904
赛任兄弟们在等她
The Silent Brothers are ready for her.

502
00:38:46,742 --> 00:38:48,160
为什么霍奇不一块来？
Why didn't Hodge come with us?

503
00:38:48,243 --> 00:38:50,162
他好多年没离开神院了
He hasn't left the Institute in years.

504
00:38:50,245 --> 00:38:51,747
有人说是诅咒
Some say it's a spell.

505
00:38:52,497 --> 00:38:53,999
他有恐旷症吧
He's agoraphobic.

506
00:39:00,047 --> 00:39:01,214
是他吗？
Is that him?

507
00:39:01,298 --> 00:39:03,258
不，那是哈罗德，扫地工
No, that's Harold, the groundskeeper.

508
00:39:04,384 --> 00:39:05,635
是他
That's him.

509
00:39:18,607 --> 00:39:21,902
你想好要经历这些了吗？
Are you sure you want to go through with this?

510
00:39:24,613 --> 00:39:27,115
我们会帮你解开回忆
We will help you to remember.

511
00:40:14,496 --> 00:40:15,872
你会吵醒亡灵的
You'll wake the dead.

512
00:40:19,876 --> 00:40:23,296
难以置信，这地方就在城市外
I can't believe this place is just outside the city.

513
00:40:38,478 --> 00:40:40,689
欢迎来到　骸骨之城
Welcome to the City of Bones.

514
00:40:47,487 --> 00:40:50,115
这是赛任兄弟汲取力量的源泉
This is where the Silent Brothers draw their power,

515
00:40:50,198 --> 00:40:53,034
暗影猎人的骸骨和骨灰
from the bones and ashes of Shadowhunters.

516
00:40:53,827 --> 00:40:55,745
他们都埋在这里？
All of them are buried here?

517
00:40:55,829 --> 00:40:57,914
对，有一天
Yes. One day,

518
00:40:58,915 --> 00:41:00,709
我会在这里
that's gonna be me.

519
00:41:10,385 --> 00:41:11,845
我只能跟到这儿了
This is as far as I go.

520
00:41:11,928 --> 00:41:13,472
你不会有事的
You'll be fine.

521
00:41:15,724 --> 00:41:17,726
你之前试过吗？
So you've done this before?

522
00:41:19,352 --> 00:41:20,687
没
No.

523
00:41:33,283 --> 00:41:35,911
你必须倾听自己的内心
You must listen with your mind.

524
00:42:29,965 --> 00:42:31,216
妈？
Mom?

525
00:42:33,051 --> 00:42:34,135
妈？
Mom?

526
00:42:41,309 --> 00:42:42,686
去，去
Go. Go.

527
00:42:49,234 --> 00:42:50,819
克拉蕾，这是卢克
Clary, this is Luke,

528
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:52,696
我最好的朋友
my dearest friend.

529
00:42:52,946 --> 00:42:54,656
你可以信任他
You can trust him.

530
00:42:54,781 --> 00:42:56,283
你好，克拉蕾
Hi, Clary.

531
00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:00,495
别说
Don't tell.

532
00:43:11,631 --> 00:43:13,717
别碰那老东西
Don't touch that old thing.

533
00:43:15,510 --> 00:43:17,512
只是个旧杯子，克拉蕾
It's just an old cup, Clary.

534
00:43:24,060 --> 00:43:26,896
克拉蕾！克拉蕾，你还好吗？
Clary! Clary, are you okay?

535
00:43:27,939 --> 00:43:29,149
克拉蕾？
Clary?

536
00:43:34,821 --> 00:43:37,616
封印比预想的要强
Your block is stronger than I anticipated.

537
00:43:37,699 --> 00:43:40,368
解铃还须系铃人了
It can only be undone by the one who put it there.

538
00:43:40,702 --> 00:43:42,495
我不清楚系铃人是谁
I have no idea who put it there.

539
00:43:42,579 --> 00:43:44,289
你写出来了
You wrote it.

540
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:53,965
你记得是相反的印象
Your mind remembers the inverted image.

541
00:43:54,049 --> 00:43:56,343
要换个角度看
Just have to look at it differently.

542
00:43:57,802 --> 00:43:59,554
“贝恩”
"B-A-N-E."

543
00:44:01,264 --> 00:44:02,932
- 贝恩  - 是谁？
- Bane.    - Who?

544
00:44:03,016 --> 00:44:05,810
马格努斯·贝恩，我记得他是个术士
Magnus Bane. He's a warlock. I should have known.

545
00:44:05,894 --> 00:44:07,896
好，那找他去
Well, let's go talk to him then.

546
00:44:07,979 --> 00:44:09,481
不能这样去
Not like that.

547
00:44:10,231 --> 00:44:12,776
你需要伊莎贝尔的协助
We're gonna need some help from Isabelle.

548
00:44:13,234 --> 00:44:14,653
这是上衣
This is a top.

549
00:44:14,736 --> 00:44:16,237
是连衣裙
It's a dress.

550
00:44:18,114 --> 00:44:19,991
我穿不了
I can't pull this off.

551
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:21,826
就差双合适的鞋子…
Well, actually, with the right shoes...

552
00:44:21,910 --> 00:44:23,370
不，我是说…
No, I mean...

553
00:44:23,453 --> 00:44:26,164
这衣服太紧，像包了一层皮一样
This dress is so tight, it's like a second skin.

554
00:44:27,791 --> 00:44:30,001
你难道没有别的了吗？
Don't you have anything else?

555
00:44:30,627 --> 00:44:32,671
要是你穿得像凡人那样去的话
If you go out looking like your mundane self,

556
00:44:32,754 --> 00:44:35,048
我们接近不了马格努斯·贝恩
we won't get within a hundred feet of Magnus Bane.

557
00:44:35,131 --> 00:44:37,300
他是布鲁克林的高级术士
He's the High Warlock of Brooklyn.

558
00:44:37,384 --> 00:44:39,469
别抱怨了，过来
Now, stop complaining, come over here.

559
00:44:42,764 --> 00:44:43,932
拿着
Hold this.

560
00:44:47,018 --> 00:44:49,396
亚力克好像很讨厌我
That guy Alec doesn't like me very much.

561
00:44:49,479 --> 00:44:51,690
亚力克是我的兄弟
That guy Alec is my brother.

562
00:44:54,192 --> 00:44:56,945
杰斯知道亚力克对他的感觉吗？
Does Jace know how Alec feels about him?

563
00:44:58,905 --> 00:45:00,740
很明显吗？
Is it that obvious?

564
00:45:00,824 --> 00:45:03,034
这真没什么大不了的
It's really not that big of a deal.

565
00:45:03,118 --> 00:45:04,994
对我也一样
It isn't to me either.

566
00:45:05,745 --> 00:45:07,214
但对克拉夫不同
But it is to the Clave.

567
00:45:07,214 --> 00:45:08,623
规则不是我定的
I don't make the rules.

568
00:45:11,459 --> 00:45:13,628
看，现在多漂亮
See? You look pretty.

569
00:45:15,088 --> 00:45:16,500
干嘛要穿得这么妖艳
How is being dressed like a hooker

570
00:45:16,500 --> 00:45:17,549
会帮我找到妈妈？
gonna help me find my mom?

571
00:45:17,632 --> 00:45:20,009
放松点，那些只是我的衣服而已
Easy now, those are my clothes.

572
00:45:20,802 --> 00:45:22,220
亚力克，她看上去漂亮吧？
Doesn't she look great, Alec?

573
00:45:22,303 --> 00:45:23,451
她看上去就像
She looks like someone

574
00:45:23,451 --> 00:45:25,849
留电话号码在浴室墙上的人
whose phone number should be on a bathroom wall.

575
00:45:31,104 --> 00:45:32,981
我觉得你很漂亮
I think you look great.

576
00:45:47,746 --> 00:45:49,831
等等，我来过这里
Wait, I've been here.

577
00:46:20,278 --> 00:46:21,738
- 等等  - 怎么了？
- Wait.     - What?

578
00:46:30,079 --> 00:46:31,539
这样更好点？
Is that better?

579
00:46:31,623 --> 00:46:32,957
更好了
It's better.

580
00:46:47,472 --> 00:46:49,015
嘿，嘿，嘿
Well, well, well.

581
00:46:49,265 --> 00:46:50,433
瞧瞧这儿
Look-a here.

582
00:46:50,558 --> 00:46:53,228
什么风把人神的孩子们吹到这儿
I don't remember inviting any children of the Nephilim.

583
00:46:53,311 --> 00:46:56,105
马格努斯·贝恩，我们要谈谈
Magnus Bane. We need to talk.

584
00:46:56,564 --> 00:46:57,982
我不喜欢你们
You know I don't like you guys.

585
00:46:58,066 --> 00:46:59,408
但我还让你们待在这儿
But I'll let you stay,

586
00:46:59,408 --> 00:47:01,277
只是因为这火辣宝贝
but only because of the hot one.

587
00:47:01,361 --> 00:47:02,946
- 谢谢  - 谢谢
- Thanks. - Thank you.

588
00:47:03,029 --> 00:47:04,113
什么？
What?

589
00:47:05,323 --> 00:47:06,741
我说的是他
I meant him.

590
00:47:06,991 --> 00:47:08,660
蓝眼睛的那位
The one with the blue eyes.

591
00:47:11,538 --> 00:47:13,498
还有克拉蕾
And because of Clary.

592
00:47:13,581 --> 00:47:15,708
等等，你怎么知道她名字？
Wait. How do you know her name?

593
00:47:15,792 --> 00:47:17,252
跟我来
Come with me.

594
00:47:21,130 --> 00:47:23,049
- 你妈妈呢？  - 她失踪了
- Where's your mother? - She's missing.

595
00:47:24,425 --> 00:47:26,052
原来如此
That explains it.

596
00:47:27,679 --> 00:47:29,440
她每年都带你来这儿
Every year, she brought you here.

597
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:31,099
从来没有漏过一次
She never missed an appointment.

598
00:47:32,684 --> 00:47:35,728
我在你身上下的咒语是最成功的
Not every spell turns out as perfect as the one I did on you.

599
00:47:38,606 --> 00:47:41,025
一旦你开始画天使图符
As soon as you started drawing the angelic rune,

600
00:47:41,109 --> 00:47:43,528
说明你的记忆又回来了
it was a sign your memory was surfacing.

601
00:47:43,611 --> 00:47:45,196
我将此咒深藏在你记忆中
I had built that into your mind

602
00:47:45,280 --> 00:47:47,740
她就能适时带你回来封印
so that she knew when to bring you back.

603
00:47:48,032 --> 00:47:49,993
暗影世界里的一切，你都会忘记
What you saw from the shadow world,

604
00:47:50,076 --> 00:47:52,245
即使你看过
you would forget, even as you saw it.

605
00:47:52,996 --> 00:47:54,122
可你越长大
But as you grew older,

606
00:47:54,122 --> 00:47:56,082
你需要封印的次数也越来越多
you needed my treatment more frequently.

607
00:47:56,541 --> 00:47:58,543
她知道有一天非得告诉你
She knew she had to tell you one day,

608
00:47:58,626 --> 00:47:59,794
但想等你准备好后
but until you were ready,

609
00:48:00,128 --> 00:48:02,204
她想封印回忆
she wanted to keep the block on your mind.

610
00:48:02,204 --> 00:48:03,798
这就是她想做的
It was exactly how she wanted it.

611
00:48:11,097 --> 00:48:13,057
我们要在这儿待多久？
How long do you think we're gonna be here?

612
00:48:13,141 --> 00:48:14,350
西蒙，放松点，好吗？
Relax, Simon, okay?

613
00:48:20,481 --> 00:48:22,233
别喝！
Don't drink that!

614
00:48:23,776 --> 00:48:26,070
西蒙！西蒙！
Simon! Simon!

615
00:48:28,656 --> 00:48:30,158
时间会消磨封印
It'll wear off over time.

616
00:48:30,241 --> 00:48:32,744
现在已经磨去了，要么你不会来这儿
It's already wearing off, or you wouldn't be here.

617
00:48:32,827 --> 00:48:34,329
我还是记不起来
I need to remember.

618
00:48:34,412 --> 00:48:35,826
我妈没有多少时间了
My mom doesn't have time.

619
00:48:35,826 --> 00:48:38,166
求你了，你肯定能做点什么
Please, there must be something you can do.

620
00:48:45,048 --> 00:48:48,509
你就是买我母亲画的人
You're the one who's been buying all my mom's paintings.

621
00:48:50,386 --> 00:48:52,513
你为什么每幅都买？
Why did you buy all of them?

622
00:48:52,597 --> 00:48:53,973
我清楚她需要钱
I knew she needed the money.

623
00:48:54,057 --> 00:48:55,475
你甚至有我爸爸的画像
You even have a portrait of my dad.

624
00:48:57,936 --> 00:48:59,520
那不是你爸
That's not your dad.

625
00:48:59,604 --> 00:49:01,356
他只是战死在伊朗的一名士兵
He's a soldier who died in Iraq.

626
00:49:01,439 --> 00:49:03,358
乔丝琳从没见过他
Jocelyn never even met the guy.

627
00:49:03,441 --> 00:49:05,109
有人请她画的
She was asked to paint his portrait,

628
00:49:05,109 --> 00:49:06,778
但这对一位寡妇来说太痛苦了
but it was too painful for the widow.

629
00:49:06,861 --> 00:49:08,473
她保留着画，所以…
She kept the picture so...

630
00:49:08,473 --> 00:49:10,365
她就能假装他是我爸爸
She could pretend he was my dad.

631
00:49:12,325 --> 00:49:14,285
她做的一切都是为了你
Everything she did, she did for you.

632
00:49:14,369 --> 00:49:15,954
你妈妈生命中的一切：
Your mother's whole existence,

633
00:49:16,037 --> 00:49:17,997
逃跑，躲藏，谎言
the running, the hiding, the lies,

634
00:49:18,081 --> 00:49:19,958
都是为了你的安全
were to keep you safe.

635
00:49:20,625 --> 00:49:23,127
她有跟我说过什么真话吗？
Was anything she ever told me true?

636
00:49:25,254 --> 00:49:28,216
你头脑里藏着一幅宝藏图，克拉蕾
There's a treasure map inside your head, Clary.

637
00:49:28,299 --> 00:49:30,969
找到圣杯，它能带你找到你妈妈
Find the Cup, and it will lead you to your mother.

638
00:49:31,052 --> 00:49:32,595
他们把西蒙带走了
They've taken Simon.

639
00:49:32,679 --> 00:49:34,347
- 谁？  - 吸血鬼
- Who?   - Vampires.

640
00:49:36,557 --> 00:49:38,059
别忘了
Just remember,

641
00:49:38,142 --> 00:49:41,270
你妈妈躲避的正是暗影猎人
it was Shadowhunters your mother was running from.

642
00:49:42,689 --> 00:49:44,482
我们去找西蒙
Let's go find Simon.

643
00:49:48,820 --> 00:49:51,030
我们不能闯进吸血鬼的老巢，我们从没试过
We can't break into a vampire's lair, we never learned.

644
00:49:51,114 --> 00:49:53,700
- 又开始了你  - 杰斯，这你知道的
- Don't start again. - Jace, you know the rules.

645
00:49:53,783 --> 00:49:54,943
伙计，我们来这干嘛？
Guys, what are we doing here?

646
00:49:54,943 --> 00:49:56,452
我们不是要找西蒙吗？
I thought we were trying to find Simon.

647
00:49:56,536 --> 00:49:58,955
我们知道他在哪，只是需要先拿些东西
We know where he is. We just need to pick up a few things.

648
00:50:01,374 --> 00:50:03,543
这是什么？你们和教堂有某种约定？
What is this, some kind of deal you have with the church?

649
00:50:05,128 --> 00:50:06,858
邪灵在世界各地都有
Demons exist all across the world

650
00:50:06,858 --> 00:50:08,589
而且外形各异
in their varying, different forms.

651
00:50:08,923 --> 00:50:11,676
暗影猎人从不单信某个宗教
Shadowhunters cling to no particular religion,

652
00:50:11,759 --> 00:50:14,345
因此，所有宗教都能协助我们作战
and in turn all religions assist us in our battle.

653
00:50:14,429 --> 00:50:17,432
我们自如穿梭在犹太教堂
We could have as easily gone to a Jewish synagogue

654
00:50:17,515 --> 00:50:19,017
或神道教塔…
or a Shinto temple or...

655
00:50:21,602 --> 00:50:22,979
在这
Here it is.

656
00:50:30,111 --> 00:50:32,613
在每个教堂的祭坛底下…
Beneath every altar in every church...

657
00:50:34,407 --> 00:50:36,159
都能找到这个
you'll find this.

658
00:50:48,796 --> 00:50:50,465
那你们信仰什么？
So, what do you believe in?

659
00:50:50,548 --> 00:50:52,216
我信仰自己
I believe in myself.

660
00:50:52,300 --> 00:50:53,676
我知道杀死邪灵是我的职责
I know my job is to kill demons.

661
00:50:53,676 --> 00:50:55,386
其它我一概不信
I don't have to believe in anything else.

662
00:50:55,470 --> 00:50:56,721
那天使拉齐尔呢？
What about the Angel Raziel?

663
00:50:56,721 --> 00:50:57,972
那是美丽的传说
Yeah, makes for a nice story.

664
00:50:58,056 --> 00:50:59,807
- 但霍奇说…  - 是啊，霍奇
- But Hodge thinks... - Yeah, Hodge.

665
00:51:00,099 --> 00:51:01,559
他还有很多没说
He needs to get out more.

666
00:51:02,143 --> 00:51:04,312
- 我原以为…  - 听着，我一直在猎杀邪灵
- I thought... - Listen, I've been hunting demons

667
00:51:04,395 --> 00:51:05,688
已经花掉了我三分之一的生命
for over a third of my life,

668
00:51:05,772 --> 00:51:08,399
到目前为止，从未见过天使
and in all that time, I've never seen an angel.

669
00:51:08,649 --> 00:51:09,776
这儿
Here.

670
00:51:11,152 --> 00:51:12,820
这，你拿这个
Here, you take this one.

671
00:51:14,489 --> 00:51:15,865
我不会…
I don't...

672
00:51:16,324 --> 00:51:17,658
这，我教你
Here, let me show you.

673
00:51:17,742 --> 00:51:20,536
这是一把杀吸血鬼的枪，必须瞄准他们的心脏
It's a vampire gun. Must pierce the heart.

674
00:51:20,828 --> 00:51:23,081
推上来，对着胸膛
Push it up against the chest.

675
00:51:23,414 --> 00:51:24,499
开火
Fire.

676
00:51:27,502 --> 00:51:29,670
再装枪 重发
Recharge. Then you're good to go again.

677
00:51:37,929 --> 00:51:39,097
死人客栈？
Hotel of Death?

678
00:51:39,180 --> 00:51:41,140
他们也有幽默感
You can't say they don't have a sense of humor.

679
00:51:41,224 --> 00:51:42,350
快点
Come on.

680
00:51:46,562 --> 00:51:48,606
- 她怎么办？  - 她很勇敢
- What is it about her? - She's brave.

681
00:51:48,689 --> 00:51:50,566
我们暗影猎人都勇敢
We're Shadowhunters, we're all brave.

682
00:51:50,650 --> 00:51:52,401
她不像我们那样抚养长大，她不同
She wasn't raised like us, she's different.

683
00:51:52,902 --> 00:51:55,029
她会连累我们被杀
She's gonna get us all killed.

684
00:52:56,257 --> 00:52:58,092
是西蒙的衬衫
Simon's shirt.

685
00:53:30,458 --> 00:53:31,667
他在上面
He's up here.

686
00:53:37,465 --> 00:53:38,799
西蒙
Simon.

687
00:53:49,268 --> 00:53:51,854
- 我的天，我的天，西蒙  - 克拉蕾
- Oh, my God, oh, my God, Simon. - Clary.

688
00:53:57,818 --> 00:53:59,820
不，我能触到他了！
No, I can feel him!

689
00:54:01,113 --> 00:54:03,699
搭把手 快点，快点
Give me a hand. Come on, come on.

690
00:54:05,201 --> 00:54:06,661
这该死的靴子！
These damn boots!

691
00:54:09,330 --> 00:54:10,414
这儿
Here.

692
00:54:10,498 --> 00:54:11,624
好
Here you go.

693
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:14,961
- 快点  - 伙计，稳住
- Come on. - Guys, steady.

694
00:54:19,715 --> 00:54:20,925
慢点
Slowly.

695
00:54:31,978 --> 00:54:33,062
他还活着！
He's alive!

696
00:54:33,271 --> 00:54:34,313
小心
Careful.

697
00:54:36,732 --> 00:54:39,610
快走，他们要的不是我
Go on. Get out. They don't want me.

698
00:54:39,694 --> 00:54:41,696
要的是你，他们要的是圣杯
They want you, they want the Cup.

699
00:54:57,586 --> 00:54:59,088
- 快点，走  - 天啊
- Come on. Let's go. - Oh, God.

700
00:54:59,422 --> 00:55:00,756
快！
Let's go!

701
00:55:03,801 --> 00:55:05,136
不，这儿
No, here.

702
00:55:15,604 --> 00:55:17,148
- 这儿！  - 走！
- In here! - Go!

703
00:55:33,622 --> 00:55:34,874
杰斯
Jace.

704
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:17,208
你身后！
Behind you!

705
00:56:42,024 --> 00:56:43,692
快点！快点！
Come on! Come on!

706
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:17,685
克拉蕾！
Clary!

707
00:57:43,085 --> 00:57:44,795
他们人数太多
There's too many of them.

708
00:57:44,879 --> 00:57:46,630
抱点信念
Have a little faith.

709
00:58:15,910 --> 00:58:17,119
跑！
Run!

710
00:58:30,758 --> 00:58:32,843
杰斯，给我把短刀
Jace, I need a knife.

711
00:58:35,513 --> 00:58:37,431
- 日出  - 快走
- The sun. - Let's go.

712
00:58:48,025 --> 00:58:49,276
帮西蒙
You help Simon.

713
00:59:03,374 --> 00:59:04,375
克拉蕾！
Clary!

714
00:59:07,795 --> 00:59:09,046
抓住！
Hold on!

715
00:59:10,130 --> 00:59:11,298
克拉蕾！
Clary!

716
00:59:22,685 --> 00:59:24,019
谢谢
Thank you.

717
00:59:27,273 --> 00:59:28,899
你救了西蒙
For saving Simon.

718
00:59:42,663 --> 00:59:45,499
- 还好吗？  - 我没事，我没事
- Are you okay? - I'm okay, I'm okay.

719
01:00:04,852 --> 01:00:05,936
克拉蕾
Clary.

720
01:00:07,479 --> 01:00:08,731
能和你谈谈吗？
Can I talk to you?

721
01:00:08,939 --> 01:00:11,525
行，我正要去看西蒙
Yeah, I was just gonna go see Simon.

722
01:00:13,861 --> 01:00:16,238
- 我希望你离开这儿  - 什么？
- I want you to leave here. - What?

723
01:00:16,322 --> 01:00:17,740
你差点让我们送死
You almost got us killed.

724
01:00:18,699 --> 01:00:20,409
对不起，我们别无选择
I'm sorry, we didn't have a choice.

725
01:00:20,492 --> 01:00:22,036
要救西蒙，而杰斯…
I mean, we had to save Simon, and Jace...

726
01:00:22,119 --> 01:00:24,204
杰斯应该拯救世界
Jace thinks he needs to save the world.

727
01:00:24,830 --> 01:00:27,750
但你没鼓励他这么做
But you don't need to encourage him to do it.

728
01:00:27,833 --> 01:00:28,800
这就是你们要做的
But that's what you guys do.

729
01:00:28,884 --> 01:00:32,671
对，我们　要做的
Yes, us. What we do.

730
01:00:33,088 --> 01:00:35,090
我们是团队，你是累赘
We're a team, you're deadweight.

731
01:00:36,050 --> 01:00:38,302
- 凡人  - 我不是凡人
- A mundane. - I'm not a mundane.

732
01:00:39,428 --> 01:00:41,535
你要是表现得有半点勇敢
And if you were half as brave as you pretend to be,

733
01:00:41,535 --> 01:00:42,306
就得承认…
you'd admit that...

734
01:00:42,389 --> 01:00:43,724
什么？
What?

735
01:00:44,183 --> 01:00:45,886
你承认你爱上了杰斯
You'd admit that you're in love with Jace,

736
01:00:45,886 --> 01:00:47,353
这才是千真万确的
and that's what this is really about.

737
01:00:49,063 --> 01:00:52,066
你敢再这样说一下…
If you ever say anything like that again...

738
01:00:53,400 --> 01:00:55,027
我定杀死你
I'll kill you.

739
01:01:21,345 --> 01:01:23,806
- 我晕了多久？  - 一整天
- How long was I out? - All day.

740
01:01:23,889 --> 01:01:25,391
你的眼镜
Found your glasses.

741
01:01:25,474 --> 01:01:27,434
- 有一边镜片裂了  - 嗯
- One of the lenses cracked. - Yeah.

742
01:01:36,485 --> 01:01:38,195
好神奇
How weird.

743
01:01:41,031 --> 01:01:42,908
我似乎不需要它了
I don't seem to need them anymore.

744
01:01:45,953 --> 01:01:48,539
那你在画什么？
So, what are you drawing?

745
01:01:49,873 --> 01:01:51,208
没什么
Nothing.

