that allows us to expose demons.

778
01:04:24,862 --> 01:04:26,864
那巴赫也是个暗影猎人咯？
So Bach was a Shadowhunter?

779
01:04:26,947 --> 01:04:28,991
- 是的  - 这么说…
- Yes.        - So...

780
01:04:29,658 --> 01:04:34,204
巴赫对于邪灵们就像大蒜对于吸血鬼
Bach is to demons what garlic is to vampires.

781
01:04:35,289 --> 01:04:36,623
也对吧
Kind of.

782
01:04:36,707 --> 01:04:38,709
我是说：大蒜会被用尽
I mean, you can run out of garlic.

783
01:04:38,792 --> 01:04:40,627
但音乐却无止境
You can't really run out of music.

784
01:04:44,298 --> 01:04:46,633
那里放着你的玩意吗？
Is that where you keep all your toys?

785
01:04:48,468 --> 01:04:49,970
有趣得多
It's way more fun.

786
01:04:50,345 --> 01:04:51,597
来吧
Come on.

787
01:04:51,680 --> 01:04:53,348
这是穿梭门
It's a portal.

788
01:04:53,432 --> 01:04:55,684
像百慕大一样的自然现象
Like the Bermuda Triangle, it's a natural phenomenon.

789
01:04:55,767 --> 01:04:57,644
神院围绕它而建
The Institute was built around it.

790
01:04:58,061 --> 01:05:01,315
据说神院是纽约最早的建筑
Some say that the Institute was the first building in New York.

791
01:05:02,733 --> 01:05:03,775
所以它…
So it's...

792
01:05:03,859 --> 01:05:06,194
空间不都只是直线型的
Dimensions aren't all just straight lines.

793
01:05:06,278 --> 01:05:07,905
也会有弯曲
There's bends,

794
01:05:07,988 --> 01:05:09,573
折叠，凹角
folds and nooks.

795
01:05:10,157 --> 01:05:12,868
有点难以解释，不过
It's a little bit difficult to explain, but

796
01:05:13,118 --> 01:05:16,663
穿梭门能带你到任何你想去的地方
the Portal can take you wherever you want to go in this dimension.

797
01:05:18,999 --> 01:05:21,001
一旦穿过表面
So, as soon as you break that surface,

798
01:05:21,084 --> 01:05:23,503
你就会被送到你心底最深处
you're transported to wherever your deepest thoughts lie.

799
01:05:23,587 --> 01:05:24,630
那意味着…
So that means...

800
01:05:24,713 --> 01:05:26,423
- 我妈妈…  - 等下
- My mom... - Wait.

801
01:05:27,174 --> 01:05:29,927
我们训练一生才懂得使用它
We spend our entire lives training how to use it,

802
01:05:30,010 --> 01:05:32,512
进入前要先想象一下所去之处
visualizing where it will take us before we step into it,

803
01:05:32,596 --> 01:05:34,932
那必须要非常集中精力
and that takes incredible focus.

804
01:05:38,352 --> 01:05:41,104
如果没有经过正确训练而进入的话
If you were to step into it without the proper training,

805
01:05:41,188 --> 01:05:42,966
你将永无安定
you could end up in limbo,

806
01:05:42,966 --> 01:05:44,942
永生困在记忆之中
lost in your own mind forever.

807
01:05:48,070 --> 01:05:49,237
这儿
Here.

808
01:05:49,321 --> 01:05:51,114
我做给你看
Let me show you.

809
01:05:51,198 --> 01:05:52,491
快点
Come on.

810
01:05:55,369 --> 01:05:56,536
别偷看
No peeking.

811
01:06:33,699 --> 01:06:35,075
很酷吧，对吧？
Pretty cool, isn't it?

812
01:06:36,118 --> 01:06:37,577
现在…
Now...

813
01:06:38,412 --> 01:06:40,789
你和我…
You and I...

814
01:06:41,331 --> 01:06:42,958
要庆祝你的生日
Have a birthday to celebrate.

815
01:06:43,041 --> 01:06:44,376
你怎么知道？
How did you know?

816
01:06:44,459 --> 01:06:47,170
我之前找你，就查到过
Research. When I was trying to find you.

817
01:06:51,717 --> 01:06:53,635
不会有人来这儿
No one comes up here anymore.

818
01:06:53,719 --> 01:06:55,429
这里属于我们
We have the place to ourselves.

819
01:06:56,179 --> 01:06:58,390
美得窒息了
This is breathtaking.

820
01:07:20,454 --> 01:07:21,830
抱歉，没有蛋糕
Sorry there's no cake.

821
01:07:21,913 --> 01:07:24,166
我原本就没期望
Well, I was expecting nothing,

822
01:07:24,249 --> 01:07:25,917
这已很棒了
so this is great.

823
01:07:26,710 --> 01:07:29,504
不过，每个人都该在生日那天得到些什么
Well, everyone should get something for their birthday.

824
01:07:33,967 --> 01:07:35,677
你生日得到什么？
What did you get?

825
01:07:35,761 --> 01:07:37,763
大多数是武器
Weapons mostly.

826
01:07:39,306 --> 01:07:40,891
希望没让你吃惊
I'm sure that doesn't surprise you.

827
01:07:40,974 --> 01:07:42,809
现在没有什么会让我吃惊
At this point, nothing really does.

828
01:07:45,729 --> 01:07:48,231
当我九岁时…
When I was nine...

829
01:07:49,566 --> 01:07:51,318
我父亲送了我一只隼
My father gave me a falcon.

830
01:07:51,610 --> 01:07:53,278
他要我让它听话
He told me to make it obedient.

831
01:07:53,361 --> 01:07:55,489
我本该弄瞎那只鸟
I was supposed to keep the bird blind,

832
01:07:55,572 --> 01:07:57,657
但我做不到
but I couldn't bring myself to do it.

833
01:07:58,533 --> 01:08:00,747
相反的是，我抚摸它的翅膀
Instead, I touched and stroked its wings

834
01:08:00,747 --> 01:08:01,828
直到它信任我
until it trusted me.

835
01:08:02,120 --> 01:08:04,081
我以为完美地驯服了它
I tamed it to perfection.

836
01:08:05,165 --> 01:08:06,763
我把它带给父亲
I took it to my father,

837
01:08:06,763 --> 01:08:09,628
希望父亲为我所做的感到骄傲
expecting him to be proud of what I'd done.

838
01:08:10,003 --> 01:08:11,755
他说：
He said,

839
01:08:12,005 --> 01:08:14,091
“我是要你让他听话”
"I told you to make it obedient.

840
01:08:15,175 --> 01:08:17,052
“不是要你教它爱你”
"Instead, you taught it to love you.

841
01:08:17,427 --> 01:08:19,304
“你没有驯服它，你毁了它”
"You didn't tame it, you broke it."

842
01:08:20,430 --> 01:08:22,974
他带走鸟，并割了它的脖子
Then he took the bird and he broke its neck.

843
01:08:24,684 --> 01:08:26,937
我当时哭了整整一夜，此后再没哭过
I cried all night and I never cried again.

844
01:08:27,437 --> 01:08:29,272
你原谅他吗？
Did you ever forgive him?

845
01:08:30,816 --> 01:08:32,692
他这么做是要我强大
He did it to make me stronger.

846
01:08:38,240 --> 01:08:39,741
那是你名字维兰德的意义吗？
Does that stand for Wayland?

847
01:08:46,456 --> 01:08:47,833
午夜
Midnight.

848
01:08:48,375 --> 01:08:49,793
瞧瞧这些
Watch this.

849
